--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Bundled source (headers) — LiteRT
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The `third_party/litert-v2.1.4/` directory contains C header files and
supporting build configuration pinned from:

  LiteRT 2.1.4
  https://github.com/google-ai-edge/LiteRT
  Copyright 2024-2026 Google LLC

Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0; see
third_party/litert-v2.1.4/LICENSE for the upstream copy. The Rust FFI bindings
in `litert-sys/src/bindings/` are machine-generated from these headers via
bindgen.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Downloaded prebuilt binaries — LiteRT-LM
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
At build time, `litert-sys` downloads a set of prebuilt shared libraries
(libLiteRt.{so,dylib,dll} + accelerator plugins) pinned by SHA-256 from:

  LiteRT-LM v0.10.2
  https://github.com/google-ai-edge/litert-lm
  Copyright 2024-2026 Google LLC

These binaries are redistributed under the Apache License, Version 2.0. They
are not bundled inside the published crates; `litert-sys/build.rs` fetches
them on first build and caches them under `$XDG_CACHE_HOME/litert-sys/`.

For Android targets, the core runtime (`libLiteRt.so`) is additionally fetched
from the upstream Google Maven artifact:

  com.google.ai.edge.litert:litert:2.1.4
  https://dl.google.com/android/maven2/com/google/ai/edge/litert/litert/

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party Rust crates used at build time
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The build dependencies (bindgen, ureq, sha2, zip, serde, serde_json, dirs,
thiserror) are listed in Cargo.toml and pulled from crates.io under their
respective open-source licenses.
